article.headline: Vermont 77, New Hampshire 60
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. -- Four McGlynn scored 20 points and Vermont defeated New Hampshire 77-60 on Sunday. The Catamounts (13-10, 7-2 America East Conference) scored 22 points off of 15 turnovers, and protected the ball themselves, turning it over just eight times. Vermont trailed 47-43 with 16:56 to go before going on a 13-2 run. Brian Voelkel's three-point play put the Catamounts up 56-49 with 11:24 remaining. Vermont pushed its lead to 69-60 with 4:13 to play and finished scoring eight straight. New Hampshire (7-13, 2-7) missed all seven of its shots the rest of the way. Matt Glass and Sandro Carissimo added 14 points each for the Catamounts, who won their fourth in a row and seventh of their last eight. One game after shooting a season-best 12 3-pointers, New Hampshire went 8 of 23 from long range against Vermont. Chandler Rhoads led the Wildcats with 16 points.
